radiographic_examinations.findings: Trace left pleural effusion and bibasilar atelectasis; liver unremarkable with trace perihepatic free fluid; no biliary duct dilatation or gallstones; mild edema within the pancreatic head and body; homogeneous enhancement of the pancreas; pancreatic duct divisum variant; unremarkable spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, gastrointestinal tract, and no lymph node enlargement; patent vascular structures.
Normal gallbladder; no intra- or extrahepatic biliary ductal dilatation; pancreas obscured by overlying bowel gas.
